<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicName LSID="ACEE23D9-9651-5C4C-B3AF-80339FD4C9D7" authority="Weddellia series Xingyiensia L. D. Duan &amp; D. H. Yin, ser. nov." authorityName="series Xingyiensia L. D. Duan &amp; D. H. Yin, ser. nov." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elatostema subsp. section" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Weddellia" species="xingyiense" subSpecies="section">Elatostema section Weddellia series Xingyiensia L.D.Duan &amp; D.H.Yin, ser. nov.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Mid-vein impressed, margin revolute, pistillate inflorescence peduncle dichotomously branched. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Typus seriei</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elatostema xingyiense" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xingyiense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Elatostema xingyiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.D. Duan &amp; D.H. Yin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="relationship">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Relationship.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
The staminate capitula of the species is long peduncelate, as such this new series is closely related to ser. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elatostema" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="series" series="Sublinearia">Elatostema Sublinearia</taxonomicName>
W.T. Wang (
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, WT" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Botanical Laboratory of North-Eastern Forestry Institute" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 96" publicationUrl="https://kns.cnki.net/kcms/detail/detail.aspx?dbcode=CJFD&amp;dbname=CJFD7984&amp;filename=MBZW198002000&amp;v=7OWzEuHRbOu%25mmd2BLQz9iy12OflJtAMh8Xq2RSh39nxP06zEhlhEvtIZBT4ZYl1dmTuK" refId="B6" refString="Wang, WT, 1980. Classificatio specierum sinicarum Elatostematis (Urticaceae). Bulletin of Botanical Laboratory of North-Eastern Forestry Institute 7: 1 - 96, https://kns.cnki.net/kcms/detail/detail.aspx?dbcode=CJFD&amp;dbname=CJFD7984&amp;filename=MBZW198002000&amp;v=7OWzEuHRbOu%25mmd2BLQz9iy12OflJtAMh8Xq2RSh39nxP06zEhlhEvtIZBT4ZYl1dmTuK" title="Classificatio specierum sinicarum Elatostematis (Urticaceae)." url="https://kns.cnki.net/kcms/detail/detail.aspx?dbcode=CJFD&amp;dbname=CJFD7984&amp;filename=MBZW198002000&amp;v=7OWzEuHRbOu%25mmd2BLQz9iy12OflJtAMh8Xq2RSh39nxP06zEhlhEvtIZBT4ZYl1dmTuK" volume="7" year="1980">Wang 1980</bibRefCitation>
). It also has similarity to ser. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elatostema" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="series" series="Melanocarpa">Elatostema Melanocarpa</taxonomicName>
W.T. Wang with its achene fawn, ovoid, longitudinally 4(-5)-ribbed and tuberculate (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/jse.12008_3" author="Wang, WT" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Systematics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" pagination="225 - 228" refId="B8" refString="Wang, WT, 2013. Five new series, eleven new species, and one new variety of Elatostema (Urticaceae) from China. Journal of Systematics and Evolution 51 (2): 225 - 228, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/jse.12008_3" title="Five new series, eleven new species, and one new variety of Elatostema (Urticaceae) from China." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/jse.12008_3" volume="51" year="2013">Wang 2013</bibRefCitation>
). However, the new series differs from these two series with regards to the following features: leaf mid-vein impressed, the margin revolute (compared to the mid-vein flat and margin flat in ser. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elatostema" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="series" series="Melanocarpa">Elatostema Melanocarpa</taxonomicName>
and ser. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elatostema" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="series" series="Sublinearia">Elatostema Sublinearia</taxonomicName>
); pistillate inflorescence peduncle dichotomously branched (compared to the peduncle not dichotomously branched in ser. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elatostema" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="series" series="Melanocarpa">Elatostema Melanocarpa</taxonomicName>
and ser. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Elatostema" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="series" series="Sublinearia">Elatostema Sublinearia</taxonomicName>
) (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological comparison between E. xingyiense, E. melanocarpum, E. sublineare, E. obscurinerve, E. langicuspe and E. youyangense." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/C730EE589E444F361CBFA9A537E4BC35" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" tableUuid="C730EE589E444F361CBFA9A537E4BC35">1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
